  "messages": [
    {
      "id": 1327,
      "from_id": "cec50b17:0",
      "to_id": "cec50b17:35",
      "content": "Fix a protocol bug in `templates/SYNAPSE-orchestrator.md` (and copy to `.synapse/SYNAPSE-orchestrator.md`).\n\n**Problem:** The \"Canonical Per-Task Sequence\" has step 1 as `start_task` and step 4 as `delegate_task` — but `delegate_task` already internally calls `start_task`. This creates two S-Deck task records for every delegated task.\n\n**Fix:** Rewrite the sequence so that:\n- For **delegated tasks**: `delegate_task` is the first and only task-opening call (remove the separate `start_task` step). The sequence becomes: Research/Plan (optional) → list_workers → delegate_task → wait → verify → merge → finish_task.\n- For **self-driven work** (doc edits, protocol updates done directly by the orchestrator): `start_task` is still called first, because there is no `delegate_task`.\n\nMake this distinction clear in the protocol. Also update the note in the `delegate_task` tool description row in the MCP Tools table if it mentions opening a task record, so it's unambiguous.\n\n**Work in a worktree:**\nRun: `synapse worktree create developer-35-fix-double-task`\nThen `cd .synapse/worktrees/developer-35-fix-double-task` and do all edits there.\n\nFiles to edit:\n1. `templates/SYNAPSE-orchestrator.md` — fix the sequence\n2. `.synapse/SYNAPSE-orchestrator.md` — copy of the above (per CLAUDE.md: \"Update SYNAPSE protocol: update templates/SYNAPSE*.md, then copy to .synapse/SYNAPSE*.md\")\n\nCommit both files. Report DONE.",
      "priority": 5,
